main event: Military pilots flying at 41,000 feet observed a green flare-like object passing within 100-200 yards of them before dissipating at 25,000 feet.
interesting points: The sighting occurred at 1930 hours on 30 January 1951 in close formation at a high altitude of 41,000 feet.
The green flare appeared similar to those fired from a 'Very' flare pistol and dissipated at about 25,000 feet.
No other aircraft were observed in the vicinity at the time of the incident, and both pilots provided consistent details of the observation.
The geographical coordinates at the time of the sighting were approximately 73° 50' west and 43° 30' north.
The conclusion of the report was 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation'.
